   The Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC) charters,
   regulates, and supervises national banks to ensure a safe, sound, and
   competitive banking system that supports the citizens, communities, and
   economy of the United States.
                     ___________________________________



   January 25, 2002
   Addition to the Publications List:

   The Bank Accounting Advisory Series expresses the OCC's current views
   on accounting topics of interest to national banks.
